abstract: HALIFAX, Nova Scotia, Aug. 9.--The American schooners Frank Butler and Hattie D. Linnell arrived at Arichat to-day, from North Bay, bound home. abstract: LONDON, Aug. 27.--It is reported in Berlin that a fresh attempt to kill the Czar was made on the 20th inst. The first shot missed the Czar, but the second perforated his coat. The Czarina has since been suffering from nervous prostration.

abstract: A great fire broke out at Scutari on Sunday afternoon, and, owing to the strong wind, spread with tremendous rapidity. abstract: CLARION, Penn., Aug. 30.--Mrs. Belle Feely, an insane inmate of the county jail, was burned to death in her cell yesterday, the result of a fire she had kindled with paper torn from the walls. The flames communicated to her clothing, and before assistance arrived her flesh was burned to a crisp. Mrs. Feely seems to have sought death by this horrible method, since she told the nurse in attendance that she wanted to die.
